1
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:19,200
Come here.

2
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:21,960
Let me take a cross-century photo for you.

3
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:23,320
Lin Yaozu,

4
00:01:23,320 --> 00:01:24,780
move a little bit this way.

5
00:01:28,320 --> 00:01:31,920
Being firmly loved is better than any romance.

6
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:35,920
Look at me.

7
00:01:41,960 --> 00:01:43,240
How is it?

8
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:44,170
Come take a look.

9
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:48,320
How is it?

10
00:01:48,759 --> 00:01:50,000
Not bad at all.

11
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:58,160
Old fossil, how did you enjoy watching TV last night?

12
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:00,240
There's so much stuff on TV.

13
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:01,120
Last night,

14
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:03,180
I didn't even know when I fell asleep.

15
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:05,040
The world is huge.

16
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:07,120
Just keep watching.

17
00:02:10,639 --> 00:02:11,920
I really can't imagine

18
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:14,240
without your sacrifices,

19
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:16,160
what the world would be like.

20
00:02:16,920 --> 00:02:18,980
It should be everyone's sacrifices.

21
00:02:19,920 --> 00:02:21,320
Oh, my.

22
00:02:21,320 --> 00:02:24,960
Who was crying while watching TV yesterday?

23
00:02:25,760 --> 00:02:26,560
Well,

24
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:29,250
the programs on TV were just too touching.

25
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:31,320
How did you know I was crying?

26
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:36,520
But you can rest assured now.

27
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:40,040
But I saw on TV that

28
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:41,520
in this world right now,

29
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:43,560
many places are still suffering from war.

30
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:45,120
Some people are even homeless,

31
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:46,980
and some can't even afford to eat.

32
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:48,960
Yes.

33
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:51,520
Not everywhere in the world is so peaceful.

34
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:54,200
Some places are still at war.

35
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:03,120
When we were transporting supplies back then,

36
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:04,580
a bicycle was a rare thing.

37
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,560
Xiao Puxiao, let me help you.

38
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:30,480
Why haven't you set off yet?

39
00:03:30,760 --> 00:03:31,840
Well...

40
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:33,840
Let me help you.

41
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:39,440
Xiao Pumao, your mission is to transport.

42
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:41,600
What,

43
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:43,200
did you forget your mission?

44
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:45,280
How could I?

45
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:49,520
This road

46
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,640
is my mission.

47
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:53,840
Ever since this road was opened,

48
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:56,440
the Japanese planes haven't stopped bombing it.

49
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:58,240
They bomb the transport convoys

50
00:03:58,320 --> 00:03:59,560
and this road.

51
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:01,960
After they bomb it, we fix it,

52
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:05,640
so that you can deliver the supplies to the front line in time.

53
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:11,300
Why don't you stay?

54
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:14,090
I think you two look good together.

55
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:15,760
I can drive myself.

56
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:26,040
Xiao Pumao,

57
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:26,800
wear this.

58
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:31,000
Mom said

59
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,600
a throwing pouch will keep you safe on the road.

60
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:36,020
It's also my token of love.

61
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:38,640
This...

62
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:40,200
When I came back,

63
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:42,960
Grandma gave me these thousand-year-old lotus seeds.

64
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:44,690
These lotus seeds are magical.

65
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:47,020
In this chaotic world,

66
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,560
they can protect you.

67
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:52,760
Xiao Pumao.

68
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,160
This is too precious.

69
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:28,020
I can't take it.

70
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:30,400
Accept it.

71
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:31,560
Just think of it as

72
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:33,240
giving him something to look forward to,

73
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:35,200
planting a seed in his heart.

74
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:39,080
Otherwise, he won't be at ease on the road.

75
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:44,600
Tell him

76
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:45,600
I'll wait for him.

77
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,130
No matter how long it takes.

78
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:51,000
I'll wait for you to return victorious.

79
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:54,280
Take care.

80
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:16,000
Are you really willing to leave?

81
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:19,280
Oh, that girl

82
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:21,080
is so reluctant to let you go.

83
00:06:21,080 --> 00:06:23,360
She was about to cry.

84
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:26,880
How does Petofi's poem go?

85
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,200
Life is dear,

86
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,280
love is dearer.

87
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:34,000
Both can be given up

88
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:35,960
for freedom.

89
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:38,800
She didn't take the things,

90
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,659
and asked me to return them to you.

91
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:42,640
Take it.

92
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,440
She said,

93
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:53,440
no matter how long, she will wait for you to come back.

94
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:54,440
Brat.

95
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:57,000
When we win,

96
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,840
I will build her ten bamboo houses.

97
00:06:58,840 --> 00:07:00,200
Just focus on driving.

98
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:03,210
I promise to complete the task.

99
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:14,200
Go down and push.

100
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:20,120
Push hard.

101
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:22,080
It started!

102
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,160
Let's go.

103
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:32,760
Close the door.

104
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:33,720
Okay.

105
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:35,240
Sit tight.

106
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:48,480
You scared me.

107
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,800
Next time you time-travel,

108
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,360
can you tell us in advance?

109
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:55,420
How is it, Director Zhang?

110
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:57,409
Is today's room fee enough?

111
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:01,600
I calculated everything, but I still fell into your trap.

112
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:02,120
No,

113
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,760
I want to treat you to coffee.

114
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:05,720
Treat us to coffee?

115
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:09,940
Was the salary very high when you came back at that time?

116
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:10,920
Salary?

117
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:14,720
Do you mean we came back for money?

118
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:17,080
If you don't get paid for work,

119
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:19,210
you still have to support your family.

120
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:22,480
What about those who have no family,

121
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,880
and came back alone?

122
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:25,010
Is it also for money?

123
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:27,160
That's not what she meant.

124
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:29,280
She just wants to know more

125
00:08:29,280 --> 00:08:31,340
about your real situation back then.

126
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:32,360
Right,

127
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:34,600
you were just being argumentative.

128
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:36,120
Now you need money for everything,

129
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,720
and prices are so high.

130
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:39,919
You drank five or six bottles of cola that night,

131
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:41,480
which cost me more than 30 yuan.

132
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:42,320
30 yuan?

133
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,280
Wow,

134
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:46,320
that's my monthly salary.

135
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:47,640
I don't believe

136
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:50,280
your salary for returning to China for transportation is only 30 yuan.

137
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:53,140
It's not even as much as you just earned from acting.

138
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:55,280
Acting is so profitable?

139
00:08:56,880 --> 00:08:58,080
But you must know,

140
00:08:58,080 --> 00:08:59,280
in Nanyang at that time,

141
00:08:59,280 --> 00:09:02,140
everyone's living conditions were very superior.

142
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:04,260
Superior living conditions?

143
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:05,680
Yes.

144
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:09,720
Among the mechanics who returned to China, there were not only engineers and college students,

145
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:11,600
but also many children from rich families.

146
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:14,400
Do you think they would come back to suffer for 30 yuan,

147
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:15,800
or even lose their lives?

148
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:19,120
There were children from rich families?

149
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:21,920
They were in their prime at that time,

150
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:23,940
young people full of passion.

151
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:27,760
Not only that,

152
00:09:27,920 --> 00:09:29,400
you must hold a recommendation letter from the Relief Committee

153
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:30,880
or the Chamber of Commerce

154
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:31,940
to return to China.

155
00:09:32,680 --> 00:09:34,340
Are the conditions so strict?

156
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:37,360
But your time wasn't like now.

157
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,680
You didn't need to buy this and that.

158
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:40,800
Basic living conditions were enough.

159
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:41,760
Unlike now,

160
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:43,160
everything costs money.

161
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:46,880
You are really obsessed with money.

162
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:48,960
No, I'm not.

163
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,760
But what about you?

164
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:54,960
Did you bring anything valuable back?

165
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:57,600
I figure

166
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,680
it's been a hundred years.

167
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:03,920
I think there must be a lot going on with you.

168
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:05,680
Hey, I

169
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:06,560
have nothing.

170
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:07,200
I don't have anything.

171
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,000
Look, look.

172
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,000
Nothing.

173
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:09,880
Here.

174
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:11,520
Nothing here either.

175
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:13,600
There's really nothing. Really.

176
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:15,520
I really have nothing.

177
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:16,800
Do you believe it?

178
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:17,400
No.

179
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:18,160
I really

180
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:19,040
have nothing.

181
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:19,680
What treasure?

182
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:20,360
No, I really don't.
